<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./336: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-19T18:00:00-05:00">March 19, 1929—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>23. Your 27, March 14, 5 p.m. What effect will rejection have upon
                                operations in Honduras? Do you consider that it would help matters
                                to effect an exchange of notes as was done recently with
                                    Colombia?<note n="16" xml:id="d350fn16">See <ref target="frus1929v02#pg_879">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 879</ref> ff.</note> See press release of
                                February 23.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>